$interpreted: Maeok: Juan-Yun! Where's the doctor!?
Qilin Guard: Little Lord!
Qilin Guard: Someone get him some dry clothes!
Soohyeon: —Tindoiimu! Wait!
Soohyeon: I'm sorry! This is all my fault!
Tindoiimu: ...I'm the one who jumped in. How is it your fault?
Soohyeon: ......
Soohyeon: ...Do we have to be enemies?
Soohyeon: I don't like those two from the seahorse and wolf tribes... They're not good people.
Soohyeon: But I like you, Tindoiimu. You're like Yonghyeon. You're a good person.
Tindoiimu: ...What are you trying to say?

Soohyeon: I... I don't know...
I'm just saying I'd like for us to be friends.
Soohyeon: Maybe I don't have the right to say that, because of our tribes' histories, but...
Tindoiimu: Kong Soohyeon...
Soohyeon: ...Listen, I've heard rumors that If you're the next arbiter, you're going to destroy the Udumbara tree. Is that true?
Tindoiimu: ......
Tindoiimu: ...It's true.

Soohyeon: ...Of course. I understand. 
And I'm sure you understand that I'm going to have to try and stop you.
Tindoiimu: ......
Soohyeon: I understand everything.
Soohyeon: ...It's just... it's such a shame. Everything is such a shame.
Maeok: Soohyeon? Where has that child gone!?
Soohyeon: I should be getting back.
Soohyeon: I'll have someone go back and get you some fresh clothes. I don't want you to catch a cold.
Tindoiimu: (...Juan-Yun... Soohyeon... They're both the same. Prattling on and on about friendship, cooperation, alliances...)
Tindoiimu: (Why can't they see it's just impossible!?)
Tindoiimu: (...It's impossible... isn't it?)
Pang: Strange, how come we're...*hic*... the only two left?
Miranda: You idiot~ No one wants to drink with us... Hah!...

Pang: Oh yeah? I thought they all jumped into the lake or something... 
This hot-pepper booze is really spicy...
Miranda: Hah... I knew you couldn't drink... more than me... My master always said...
Pang: Always said...?

Miranda: He said a bunch of crap, that's what! *hic*
Said he'd keep in contact with me, but I've just heard a... whole lotta nothin'!
Pang: You know what's weird... is... is hearin' from someone who...*hic*... died years ago!
Pang: That's... That's scary! *hic* Why're you trying to scare me!?
Himawari: ...Would you quiet down!? I'll go with you, alright!?
Miranda: ...That's... That honey badger, and... Himawari...?
Pang: Mm... Himawari... If I were her, I'd never forgive that Sennosuke...
Miranda: Yeah, that's... obviously she wouldn't... but... but they're leaving together... right now...*hic*
Pang: No they're not...! You're crazy... I like you, but you're crazy. It's probably that...*hic*... bull guy or... or something...
Pang: He was just... looking for Himawari...

Miranda: I'm not... crazy... I know what I saw! *hic*
Let's... Let's go check it out...
Pang: How about you go check it out... and get back to me...*yawn*

Pang: I'm gonna have another...*hic*... drink...
You should bring some more booze back with you...
Miranda: (I knew something was... fishy about that girl... Damn, I shouldn't have had so much to drink...)
Himawari: ......
Miranda: (I can't tell what they're saying...)
Himawari: ...Can't you keep it down!? You want everyone to hear!?
Sennosuke: Maybe I would if you'd just learn how to cooperate with me!
Himawari: Let's get one thing clear. I am not your Alliance spy.
Himawari: I'm not going to fish out information for you, and I'm definitely not going to sell out Juan-Yun.
Himawari: Ah! My tail!
Miranda: (What... What am I seeing...)
Sennosuke: Don't be mad, I just want to make sure we're on the same page.
Sennosuke: Geez, if your disguise didn't just fall off, I might think you were really her.
Sennosuke: —Now you better buck up and remember who put you here in the first place.
Sennosuke: Ahem, I've got to get going. Don't let me down.
Sennosuke: —Himawari.
Miranda: ...What was that all about?
Himawari: You... What are you doing here!?
Miranda: I was so drunk I thought I was hallucinating, but your conversation just now sobered me right up.
Miranda: What in the—
Himawari: Shut up!
Himawari: Guh...
Miranda: Ready to talk, yet? What just—
Bull Competitor: Himawari!
Bull Competitor: What happened? Is this human causing you trouble?
Himawari: That's right! Help me kill her!
Bull Competitor: Wha... Kill her!?
Himawari: She's been pestering me, and if you care about me you'll help me kill her right now!
Himawari: Or was everything you said a lie!? All that about taking care of me, sticking by my side...!?
Bull Competitor: Of course I wasn't lying! But... but she's in the tournament! We can't harm her... It's the rules!
Himawari: I'm asking you to help me and you're thinking about rules!?
Juan-Yun: Ah, I was wondering where all my guests went. Here you are~
Himawari: Juan-Yun!
Himawari: (I... I can't let Juan-Yun know...)
Bull Competitor: Hey! Himawari just let you go, and now you're trying to go after her!?
Miranda: Let me pass! This has nothing to do with you!
Juan-Yun: Miranda, please. I don't know what Himawari did to anger you, but could you let her go this time? For me?
Miranda: ......
Miranda: (They're all helping her... Seems like I'll need to wait for another opportunity.)
Miranda: (I need to know what I just witnessed...)
